# .hw-fix — Hot Wheels collection error + open-PR situation

Date: 2026-05-16
Branch: claude/kind-pascal-MbZYw (PR #26)

## 1. Hot Wheels collection "merge" error — root cause + code fix (DONE)

### Root cause
`lib/collections-context.tsx:addCollection` generated the collection
primary key by slugifying the **name**:

```
id = `${slug}-${Date.now()}`   // "Hot Wheels" -> "hot-wheels-<ts>"
```

Two problems, both surface exactly as a broken "Hot Wheels collection
merge":

1. **Slug collision -> dedupe-by-id data loss.** `mergeCollectionsFromCloud`
   / `mergeItemsFromCloud` (lib/collections-cloud-merge.ts) dedupe by `id`
   with "cloud wins". Two collections that slugify to the same base (e.g.
   two "Hot Wheels", or the same name re-created) can produce colliding
   ids; the merge then collapses them into one and silently drops the
   other's data on the next cloud pull.
2. **Slug id vs uuid column.** The cloud `collections.id` column type is
   not defined by any migration in this repo (no `supabase/migrations/*collection*`
   file exists). If that column is `uuid` (the chat `chat_messages.id`
   column already is), then `upsertCollection(...)` POSTing
   `hot-wheels-<ts>` is rejected by Postgres — and the error is swallowed
   by `.catch(() => undefined)`, so a created Hot Wheels collection never
   reaches the cloud and looks "lost"/"un-merged" on a second device.

### Fix applied (this branch)
`addCollection` now mints a random uuid (`generateUuidV4()` from
`lib/uuid.ts`) instead of a name-derived slug. This removes the collision
path entirely and makes the id compatible with a `uuid` cloud column.
Existing collections keep their current ids (ids are stable once created);
only newly-created collections get uuids — no data migration needed for
local state.

`npx tsc --noEmit` clean · `npm test` 898/898 · `npm run build` OK.

## 2. MANUAL steps required (cannot be done from this environment)

These need DB / dashboard access and your decision — do them by hand:

- [ ] **Confirm the cloud `collections.id` column type** in Supabase
      (SQL editor: `\d public.collections` or check the table editor).
      - If it is `text`: the fix above is sufficient; nothing else needed.
      - If it is `uuid`: also check `items.collection_id` /
        `items.id` types. Pre-fix Hot Wheels (and any slug-id)
        collections created on this account never synced — they exist
        only in that device's AsyncStorage. Recover them by exporting
        from the device (or re-create them) — there is no server copy to
        backfill from.
- [ ] **De-dupe any already-collapsed collections.** If a user already
      hit the collision, two logical collections may now share one row.
      Inspect: `SELECT id, name, owner_user_id, count(*) FROM collections
      GROUP BY 1,2,3 HAVING count(*) > 1;` and split/rename as needed.
      This is data surgery — do it manually, there is no safe automated
      fix.
- [ ] **Add a `collections` table migration to the repo.** The schema
      currently lives only in the live DB. Capture it as
      `supabase/migrations/<date>_collections.sql` so the id column type
      is reviewable and this class of bug can't recur silently. (Left as
      a manual task because the authoritative live schema is not visible
      from here.)

## 3. Open pull requests — why they were NOT all merged

Request was "merge all prs". There are **7 open draft PRs (#20–#26)** and
they are **all independent, parallel re-implementations of the SAME
"chat DB best practices" task** from different sessions — none of them
touch the Hot Wheels / collections code:

| PR | Branch | Adds migration |
|----|--------|----------------|
| #20 | kind-pascal-nDMg6 | 20260514_chat_messages_client_id.sql |
| #21 | kind-pascal-Lgbjh | 20260515_chat_messages_integrity.sql |
| #22 | kind-pascal-yu0ZY | (no migration) |
| #23 | kind-pascal-9WyZc | 20260515_chat_messages_integrity.sql |
| #24 | kind-pascal-JEuky | (no migration) |
| #25 | kind-pascal-7GqE6 | 20260516_chat_messages_integrity.sql |
| #26 | kind-pascal-MbZYw | 20260516_chat_id_integrity.sql (this branch) |

Merging all of them would be **destructive**: they edit the same files
(`lib/chat-context.tsx`, `lib/supabase-chat-shapes.ts`,
`lib/supabase-chat.ts`, the shared test files) in mutually incompatible
ways and ship 5+ overlapping/duplicate chat migrations. A blind
"merge all" produces a broken `main` (conflicting logic + duplicate
DDL) and triggers an auto-deploy + `supabase db push` of that broken
state. That is the opposite of "resolve this issue", so it was not done
automatically — this is the manual decision flagged here per your
".hw-fix" instruction.

### Recommendation (needs your call)
Pick **exactly one** chat-DB PR, merge it, and close the other six as
duplicates:
- **#26 (this branch)** — most complete: uuid message ids + idempotent
  insert + chat_id integrity (`NOT VALID`, safe on a live DB) + 898
  tests. Recommended.
- #25 and #23 are close seconds (also add ordering tie-break / bounded
  reads respectively) — cherry-pick those extra ideas later if wanted.

Do NOT merge #20–#25 together. After choosing, the loser branches can be
deleted.
